<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-30T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="636" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d636">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 654.119/111</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WHR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-30T17:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1426. Your January 22, 8 p.m. The attitude you adopted in respect of
                                Swiss negotiations with England for tonnage is approved. Under
                                provisional agreement just signed with Holland<note n="3" xml:id="d636fn3">See note No. 648, Jan. 25, from the Netherland
                                    Minister, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1392">p.
                                        1392</ref>.</note> a limited <pb facs="0765" n="1599" xml:id="pg_1599"/> amount of shipping will temporarily be made
                                available to transport grain to Switzerland but it is not desired
                                that you relax your efforts to induce Switzerland to meet England’s
                                views so as to facilitate procuring ships for Swiss use not only now
                                but in the future.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>